General Accidental Release Prevention Program and Chemical-Specific Prevention Steps 

The facility has taken ail the necessary steps to comply with the accidental release prevention requirements set out under 40 CFR Part 68 for Program Level 1 processes, The facility was designed and constructed in accordance with appropriate engineering and nationally recognized design standards. The following sections describe the elements of the release prevention program that is in place. 





Emergency Response Plan 



The Greater Des Moines Energy Center employees will not respond to accidental releases of regulated substances; therefore, the Greater Des Moines Energy Center is not applicable to the requirements on ?68.95.  The Greater Des Moines has coordinated with the Local Emergency Planning Committee to be included in their emergency response plan.  The Greater Des Moines Energy Center has also coordinated with the local fire department to be included in their fire mitigation plan.



The Polk County Emergency Services and Disaster Agency is the Local Emergency Planning Committee (LEPC) with which emergency response has been coordinated. 



The telephone number of the LEPC Coordinator is (515) 283-4768.





